Package padsof

Class Long

  • java.lang.Object
    • padsof.Offer
      • padsof.Long

  • public class Long
extends Offer
    Author:
    David Cabornero and Alejandro Santorum This class allows us to create new long stay offers. These offers can specifically start in a certain day (or later) and the renter has a minimum period of the contract, unlike the short stay offers.

      • Long

        public Long​(float price,
            Apartment apartment,
            RegisteredUser owner,
            java.util.GregorianCalendar initialDate,
            int nDays,
            int nMonths,
            int nYears)
     throws OfferException,
            UserException
        This constructor allows to create a new long stay Offer
        Parameters:
        price - The price of the offer
        apartment - The apartment to be rented
        owner - The Landlord of the apartment
        initialDate - the initial date of the offer
        nDays - The minimum number of days of the contract (you also have to introduce months and years)
        nMonths - The minimum number of months of the contract (you also have to introduce days and years)
        nYears - The minimum number of years of the contract (you also have to introduce months and days)
        Throws:
        UserException - this user cannot offer
        OfferException - invalid offer operation
